  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether the blood pressure medication, diltiazem,
      will temporarily decrease the sense of smell when given in a nasal spray which will then
      reduce food intake.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      You will fast on your first visit. Complete questionnaire about taste and smell to insure you
      don't have a cold or anything that would interfere with sense of smell. Your nose will be
      checked. Blood pressure taken, and administer to you a spray with diltiazem 2, 4, 8 mg or a
      placebo. Your sense of smell will be tested at different time points.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
